(44, 20, 5, 55, 4, 13, 13, 'Troas', 'Connection through Troas', 'Both passages emphasize Troas as a significant location. Acts 20:5 mentions Troas in the context of travel, while 2 Timothy 4:13 references it as the place where Paul left his cloak.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 5, 44, 20, 6, 8, 'tarried for us at Troas', 'Journey to Troas', 'This connection highlights the journey of Paul and his companions to Troas. The SOURCE verse mentions those who ''tarried for us at Troas,'' while the TARGET passage describes their arrival and activities in Troas, emphasizing the continuity of their mission.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 5, 44, 20, 13, 15, 'tarried for us at Troas', 'Journey of Paul and Companions', 'Both passages emphasize the travel of Paul and his companions. The mention of ''trodden'' paths in Acts 20:5 connects to their subsequent journey detailed in Acts 20:13-15.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 5, 47, 2, 12, 12, 'Troas', 'Connection through Troas', 'Both passages emphasize Troas as a significant location in Paul''s ministry. Acts 20:5 mentions individuals waiting in Troas, while 2 Corinthians 2:12 highlights Paul''s arrival there to preach.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 6, 44, 12, 3, 3, 'the days of unleavened bread', 'Connection of Unleavened Bread', 'Both passages emphasize ''the days of unleavened bread,'' linking them through a shared temporal context. This connection highlights the significance of this period in the narrative.', 'keyword', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 6, 2, 12, 14, 15, 'days of unleavened bread', 'Connection of Unleavened Bread', 'This connection highlights the significance of the ''days of unleavened bread'' in Acts, which directly relates to the observance of unleavened bread in Exodus. Both passages emphasize the importance of this feast as a lasting ordinance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 6, 2, 23, 15, 15, 'days of unleavened bread', 'Connection of Unleavened Bread', 'This connection highlights the observance of the feast of unleavened bread in both passages. Acts 20:6 mentions the timing of sailing after the days of unleavened bread, paralleling Exodus 23:15''s command to keep the feast.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 6, 44, 16, 12, 12, NULL, 'Journey from Philippi to Troas', 'Both passages emphasize the journey of Paul and his companions, highlighting their time spent in Philippi before traveling to Troas. The mention of Philippi in both verses connects the locations and the timeline of their travels.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 6, 46, 5, 7, 8, 'days of unleavened bread', 'Connection of Unleavened Bread', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of unleavened bread, symbolizing purity and sincerity. Acts 20:6 mentions the days of unleavened bread, while 1 Corinthians 5:7-8 discusses being unleavened in a spiritual sense.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
