(44, 20, 7, 46, 16, 2, 2, 'first day of the week', 'Connection of Weekly Gatherings', 'This connection highlights the significance of the first day of the week for the early church. Both passages emphasize communal activities, such as breaking bread and gathering resources.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 7, 44, 2, 42, 42, NULL, 'Breaking Bread and Fellowship', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of ''breaking bread'' among the disciples. This connection highlights the communal aspect of early Christian gatherings, where teaching and fellowship were central.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 7, 43, 20, 19, 19, 'first day of the week', 'Connection of the First Day', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the first day of the week as a time of gathering for the disciples. In Acts, the disciples come together to break bread, while in John, they assemble in fear, marking a pivotal moment in their community.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 7, 43, 20, 1, 1, 'first day of the week', 'Significance of the First Day', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the first day of the week. Acts 20:7 describes a gathering for breaking bread, while John 20:1 marks the resurrection event, highlighting a pivotal moment in early Christian worship.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 7, 44, 20, 11, 11, 'break bread', 'Breaking Bread and Departure', 'Both passages emphasize the act of breaking bread, indicating a communal meal and fellowship among the disciples. Additionally, they highlight the timing of Paul''s departure, suggesting a continuity in the events of that night.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 7, 66, 1, 10, 10, 'first day of the week', 'Connection of the Lord''s Day', 'This connection highlights the significance of the first day of the week, which is also referred to as the Lord''s Day. Both passages emphasize communal gatherings and spiritual experiences occurring on this day.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 7, 42, 24, 35, 35, NULL, 'Breaking Bread Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of breaking bread, which signifies fellowship and communion among believers. This connection highlights the importance of shared meals in the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 8, 44, 1, 13, 13, NULL, 'Upper Room Gatherings', 'Both passages emphasize gatherings in an upper room, highlighting the significance of this setting for communal activities among early believers. The mention of an upper chamber in Acts 20:8 connects to the upper room in Acts 1:13, suggesting a continuity in the practice of meeting in such spaces.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
