(44, 20, 9, 41, 13, 36, 36, NULL, 'Sleeping and Vigilance', 'This connection highlights the theme of being alert versus falling asleep. Both passages emphasize the consequences of being inattentive, as Eutychus falls asleep during Paul''s preaching, while Mark warns against being found sleeping when the master returns.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 9, 40, 26, 40, 41, NULL, 'Sleep and Vigilance Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of sleep and the consequences of failing to remain vigilant. In both passages, individuals fall asleep at critical moments, leading to dire outcomes, emphasizing the struggle between the spirit and the flesh.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 9, 32, 1, 5, 6, 'being fallen into a deep sleep', 'Sleep and Danger Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of sleep in moments of peril. In both passages, individuals are asleep while critical situations unfold, leading to life-threatening circumstances.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 9, 11, 17, 19, 19, 'loft', 'Connection of Death and Revival', 'Both passages emphasize a young man in a loft who experiences death, followed by a revival. Eutychus falls from a loft and is taken up dead, while the son in 1 Kings is carried to a loft and revived. This connection highlights the theme of life restored after death.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
