(44, 20, 9, 44, 14, 19, 19, 'taken up dead', 'Death and Revival Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of presumed death in both passages. Eutychus is taken up dead after falling, while Paul is thought to be dead after being stoned.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 41, 5, 39, 39, 'for his life is in him', 'Resurrection and Life Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life after apparent death. In Acts, Paul reassures others that the young man’s ''life is in him,'' while in Mark, Jesus states the girl is ''not dead, but sleepeth.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 40, 9, 23, 24, 'for his life is in him', 'Resurrection and Life Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life after apparent death. In Acts, Paul reassures that ''his life is in him,'' while Jesus states the maid ''is not dead, but sleepeth.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 43, 11, 11, 11, 'his life is in him', 'Connection of Life and Sleep', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of life and awakening from a state resembling death. In Acts, Paul reassures that ''his life is in him,'' while in John, Jesus refers to Lazarus as ''sleepeth,'' indicating a temporary state before revival.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 43, 11, 40, 40, 'his life is in him', 'Connection of Life and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of life being restored through faith. In Acts, Paul assures that ''his life is in him,'' while in John, Jesus emphasizes belief leading to witnessing God''s glory, which can be interpreted as a form of life restoration.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 11, 17, 21, 22, 'for his life is in him', 'Revival of the Dead', 'This connection highlights the theme of revival in both passages, where a figure (Paul and Elijah) brings a lifeless person back to life. Both instances emphasize the restoration of life through divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 12, 4, 34, 35, 'for his life is in him', 'Resurrection and Restoration Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the act of restoring life to the dead. In Acts, Paul reassures the people that the boy''s ''life is in him,'' while in 2 Kings, the prophet''s actions lead to the child''s revival.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 10, 42, 7, 13, 13, NULL, 'Compassion in Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize compassion in moments of crisis. In Acts, Paul reassures those mourning by stating, ''for his life is in him,'' while in Luke, Jesus comforts a grieving mother with ''Weep not.'' This connection highlights the theme of compassion and hope in dire situations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 11, 44, 20, 7, 7, NULL, 'Breaking Bread and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the act of breaking bread in the context of fellowship and teaching. The first passage describes the continuation of Paul''s speech until dawn after breaking bread, linking it to the gathering mentioned in the second passage.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
