(44, 20, 13, 41, 6, 31, 33, 'to ship, and sailed', 'Journey and Rest Motif', 'This connection highlights the theme of travel and rest in both passages. In Acts, Paul intends to go afoot, while in Mark, Jesus invites his disciples to rest after their travels.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 15, 55, 4, 20, 20, 'Miletus', 'Connection through Miletus', 'Both passages emphasize Miletus as a significant location. Acts 20:15 mentions the arrival at Miletus, while 2 Timothy 4:20 references Trophimus being left there.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
